olb — third-party notices
==========================

This file is regenerated at release time from the real module graph with
google/go-licenses (see scripts/gen-notices.sh) and embedded into the binary via
//go:embed, so `olb --licenses` reproduces the required copyright notices and
full license texts for every linked dependency, and any dependency NOTICE
contents, regardless of how the binary is distributed.

This placeholder ships in source checkouts and development builds. A release
build overwrites it with the aggregated, authoritative notices before embedding.

Direct dependencies and their licenses (see go.mod for exact versions):

  github.com/gophercloud/gophercloud/v2      Apache-2.0
  github.com/gophercloud/utils/v2            Apache-2.0
  github.com/charmbracelet/bubbletea         MIT
  github.com/charmbracelet/bubbles           MIT
  github.com/charmbracelet/lipgloss          MIT
  github.com/aymanbagabas/go-osc52/v2        MIT
  gopkg.in/yaml.v3                           MIT and Apache-2.0

The full transitive set (including the Charm x/* modules, muesli/termenv,
mattn/go-runewidth, mattn/go-isatty, rivo/uniseg, gofrs/uuid, and others) is
entirely permissive (MIT / BSD / ISC / Apache-2.0); the go-licenses CI check is
authoritative and fails the build on any disallowed or unknown license.
